Mostly cloudy- rain on and off past 2 days
Partly cloudy- windy- heavy t-storms past weekend.  Water level: up slightly
Sunny- warm- breezy- little rain past week
Overcast- cool- breezy- algae bloom showing on calm days/protected areas- "yuck!"
Partly cloudy- warm. breezy- heavy t-storms last night
Cloudy- windy- heavy rain few days ago.  Water level: up slightly
Cloudy- cool- over 8" rain past 10 days
Cloudy- windy- very cold- raining- lake highest in past 5 years.  Lake level: very high
Clear- cool- calm- dam open over weekend to lower- lake turning over
Cool- windy- 2 days ago lake churned from very high winds
Overcast- cool- heavy rains past week
Overcast- calm- cool- water cooling quickly
Overcast- cool- ice forming overnight- then melting- 6" drawdown for winter
Sunny and hot.  Popple trees are finally blooming- but their buds are falling into the lake creating some green scum in bays.
Overcast day- had heavy rainstorms last night and early this morning.  Still plenty of popple and birch blooms falling into the lake.
Lots of rain and wind lately.  Things have really been churning.
First decent day in about two weeks.  Birch trees are dropping lots of pollen in the water.
Sunny- warm day.  Still seems to be a lot of pollen in the water.
Sunny- warm- calm day.  Pollen is slowly disappearing from sight.  May flies started hatching.
Sunny- breezy day.  Pollen disappearing but water clarity doesn't seem to be improving.
Been windy and rainy again.  Also- lake really was churned up this past holiday weekend.
On calm days one can notice algae blooms already- but it seems with the clarity remaining low this year- the weeds aren't popping up as fast.
On and off rain continued this week keeping water levels high.
Nice gentle breeze today- slightly overcast- rain finally let up a bit- algae blooms are quite evident on calm days.
Cooler- overcast day with slight breeze.  On last Tuesday I was out with a water specialist and had a reading of 4' that was taken at 6am - I thought that was pretty strange.
Sunny- breezy day.  Rain has pretty much held off for almost a solid week.  A drought   (ha ha)
Sunny- calm day.  Algae blooms are quite evident on these days.
Cloudy- breezy day.  Not much change lately.
Lake studies in conjunction with planning grants are well underway.
Lots of rain this past week pushing water levels up.
Still raining a little every day- but now it's cooling down quite a bit.
Water seems to be clearing up a bit.
Still getting rain often- but lake level is getting near normal.
Water seems to be clearing up nicely. not as much rainfall lately.
Sunny- breezy day.  The water is getting cold.
Ice on!!  can not hardly believe it- 3/4" of ice covering whole lake- earliest ever    boat frozen in.
Partly cloudy and not much rain lately.
Sunny and we need some rain.
Got some rain- but certainly not enough.  Two nights this weekend down to 28 degrees for a low.
Getting some rain- but still staying cool.
Finally got some needed rain.  Noticed first algae blooms (small scale) of the season.
Still some slight algae blooms.  Lilly pads coming up in full force.
Need some rain.  Getting pretty dry again.
This is certainly not a normal summer. fisherman report finding spawn in Panfish yet.
Algae seems to be at minimum yet- especially compared to chair of lakes in Phillips.
Not much change- still cool and dry.
On calm mornings algae blooms quite evident.
Finally got full amount of rain.  Lake level should start rising.  Algae still blooming even though water is still quite cool compared to a normal summer.
Finally starting to get some rain.  Lake temperature cooling off pretty quick.
Lake level coming up.  Plenty of rain lately.
A lot of boat traffic 2 days prior
Sunny- windy- and lots of boat traffic.
Wind was 20 MPH plus gusts.  Did not attempt to do Secchi test.  Lake level about 2 inches higher than normal.
Light breeze about 5 MPH- scattered clouds.  Lake level about 3 inches higher than normal.
Lake level about 3 inches high.  Sun visible through thin overcast.
Light breeze- clear sky- lake 1 to 2 inches higher than normal.
Windy and overcast.  Ice out was less than 2 weeks ago.
Thin overcast.  Temperature 3' deep at center of Squaw Creek culvert 72.8 degrees.
Windy- lake level at 0.78 on the gauge on the dam.
Ice went out 5-2-2014.  Loons are back.
Scattered clouds- 80 degrees- very light breeze - almost calm.
Surface water temperature 75 on main lake- 80 on Disappearing Creek.  Disappearing Creek temps 67.4 at 3'- 62.0 at 6' near bridge- 66.7 at 3' at bend- and 66.9 at 3' farthest upstream.
Ice went out 4-4-2015.  Clear sky- light breeze from southwest.

column1: 4-14-2015: 49.8 deg middle of lake at 3 feet deep
4-16-2015: 55.4 deg middle of lake- 58.8 deg at outlet of Squaw Creek culvert

column2: Very light breeze from south- almost calm.  Thin scattered clouds.
Sunny- light breeze barely enough to ripple the water.  Cool weather last two weeks- so lake temperature is low.
Solberg fully covered with ice this morning.  Squaw Creek bay had 3" ice according to an ice fisherman.
Ice went out 3-29-2016- cold weather since- 2" snow on the ground.  South breeze- scattered clouds- lots of ducks flying.
Thin overcast- light breeze from south.
Ice on Solberg this morning- but it only lasted a couple hours.
Ice out April 3- 2017.  Thin overcast- very light breeze.  Thermometer battery died after the first temperature reading.
Overcast- light breeze from west- 6" rain in the last two weeks.
Ice almost off - about 5% ice cover remaining.  Ice fully off 5/5/2018.
Clear sky- light breeze from south- two days after ice out.
Breeze from south- scattered high clouds.
8.5 inches rain from 6-12-2018 through this morning.  Lake level highest I've seen in 23 years.  Light breeze from north- cumulus clouds.
Light breeze from northwest- scattered cumulus clouds.
Thin overcast- breeze from the north.

column1: Light breeze- overcast- 43 degrees air temperature.  The temperatures are correct- it really was exactly the same temperature all the way down.

column2: Thin overcast- light breeze from south.
Breeze from south - 12 gusting 20 with thin overcast.
Breeze from west- broken cumulus clouds.
Scattered cumulus clouds- light breeze from west.  Ice on Solberg 11-21-2020.
